Narrative:
-In late January 2023, the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Southern Region Narcotics developed a confidential informant with information regarding a distributor of controlled dangerous substances in the College Park area of Prince George's County.
Initial investigation developed only the name "Carlos" for the suspect and described as a Hispanic male. CI advised “Carlos” spoke with him about selling pills for $10 each. Investigators determined based on this initial investigation that these may be pills the target "Carlos" is selling as 30 mg Percocet pills, that are likely not Percocet and are Fentanyl.
The CI contacted "Carlos" to arrange a controlled purchase of this CDS. Investigators, including Homeland Security Investigations and Prince George's County Police DEA Group 43, briefed at the Maryland State Police College Park Barrack and reviewed a possible identity for "Carlos", possible locations for his residence, and for the location of the purchase. The CI made contact with “Carlos” through text messages and phone calls to 240-772-8433. Subscriber information is pending.
Case agents, including co-case agent SA J. Nugent, met with the CI to provide them an agreed upon amount of US Currency to complete the purchase. CI was searched prior to the operation along with their vehicle. CI was provided a device by the case agents, so he could be monitored during the operation. CI made contact with "Carlos" and was directed to an apartment complex in the area of 9220 Edwards Way in Hyattsville. While case agents met with the CI, other investigators performed pre-surveillance of the area of 9220 Edwards Way and target residence, 9601 Cottrell Terr Silver Spring, Maryland.
The CI was observed entering the apartment complex parking lot and park. Investigators also observed a dark-colored Honda Passport bearing Maryland registration 1FE2341 arriving at the location. MVA checks were conducted, and it was determined the Honda is registered to Grecia Priscilla Llanos DOB 3/15/1992 of 14555 Farmcrest Pl Silver Spring, Maryland 20905. The CI was monitored during the entire meeting with the suspect. When the transaction was completed, investigators identified the suspect vehicle and initiated mobile surveillance. Due to extreme traffic in the area, contact with the suspect vehicle was lost and surveillance was discontinued. A short time later, investigators observed the Honda arriving at 9601 Cottrell Terr. Investigators were unable to determine which occupant exited the vehicle and entered the residence.
A possible suspect has been developed but is still being confirmed, however, case agents discovered who is believed to be Juan Alberto Reyes Caseres (DOB 7/26/1999), to be the suspect. MVA photographs were shown to the CI, and he was able to advise there was a similar description to “Carlos”. Case agents met with the CI and obtained the purchased CDS and debriefed them regarding the event. Evidence was brought to the College Park Barrack and stored per policy.
In addition, the CI advised the conversation with the target included purchasing additional CDS such as “rock” and purchasing firearms. The target advised the CI he will send a message with a list of firearms available.
Case agents seized one hundred (100) blue pills marked “M30” weighing 41 grams suspected Fentanyl.
Case Open.
All events occurred in Prince George's County, Maryland.

Narrative:
-In early February 2023, the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Southern Region Narcotics utilized a confidential informant to make a controlled purchase of suspected fentanyl pills from a target, “Carlos”, in the College Park / Adelphi area. “Carlos” has been potentially identified as Juan Alberto Reyes-Caseres. The CI made contact with “Carlos” to set up a time and location for the purchase. “Carlos” confirmed the location to be the same as the previous purchase, an apartment complex parking lot in the area of Adelphi, Maryland. Southern Region previously identified a possible residence for “Carlos” and placed a pole camera at the residence. “Carlos” has been using two different telephone numbers and both are being monitored via PEN / Trap and Trace devices.
Investigation team deployed to target residence and suspected location where the transaction would occur. The confidential informant met case agents and was searched as well as their vehicle. The CI was provided with a device, so their safety could be monitored during the operation. The CI was provided funds from a Homeland Security Investigations working fund to complete transaction.
The CI deployed to the area, an identified apartment complex in the Adelphi area, and surveillance units observed and identified a dark-colored Ford F-150 bearing Maryland registration 8ES9488, arrive and parked next to the CI.  The driver who was identified by the CI as “Carlos” exited the Ford and entered the CI’s vehicle. The transaction was completed and surveillance was initiated by the surveillance team on the Ford. The Ford was observed entering the parking lot of the Wawa, 9100 Riggs Rd, Hyattsville, MD 20783, and parking at gas pump #6. The surveillance team also observed the driver and the front passenger exit the vehicle and enter the Wawa. A short time later, both parties exit the Wawa, pump gas at pump #6, enter the vehicle, and drive off. Surveillance was shortly discontinued due to extreme traffic in the area. At this time, identity of suspect who performed the distribution during this instance is unknown. Investigators believe surveillance footage from a nearby convenience store may be available to assist in identifying suspect in this incident.
The CI was debriefed and provided investigators with 91 blue “M30” pills suspected Fentanyl. These pills are similar to the previous controlled purchase. The evidence was transported to College Park Barrack and processed. Evidence was weighed to be approximately 10 grams and packaged for storage at the College Park Barrack.
The CI also advised the purchase of firearms was discussed. “Carlos” stated he can obtain any firearm and is currently able to provide a “AR15”. “Carlos” did not state a price and stated he would talk his associate to confirm the details.
On 2/9/2023 investigators made contact with the shift manager at the Wawa, 9100 Riggs Rd, Hyattsville, MD 20783. Consent was given to operate the surveillance footage. Investigators were able to locate the time and cameras which captured the Ford entering the parking lot and parking at gas pump #6. Investigators observed the driver, wearing dark pants and a black hoodie, and the front passenger, wearing blue jeans, black shirt, and green jacket, exit the vehicle. Both parties enter the Wawa, make a purchase, exit the Wawa, and enter the Ford after pumping gas. At this time, the driver or the passenger do not appear to be Juan Alberto Reyes Caseres. Further investigation revealed the Ford's registered owner is Jose Wilberg Gaitan Mata (H/M DOB 06/05/1968) of 4401 52nd Pl Bladensburg, Maryland 20710. It was discovered the Ford was involved in a traffic stop on 3/9/2022 and the listed driver was identified via his Maryland driver's license as Brian Eugenio Gaitan Sanchez (H/M DOB 10/13/2002) of 4401 52nd Pl Bladensburg, Maryland 20710. It is believed Brian is Jose's son. There is no information believing Jose is involved in the distribution of these pills. After comparing the Wawa video footage and the MVA photograph of Brian, it is believed the front passenger of the Ford is Brian due to having similar facial descriptions.
Case Open.
All events occurred in Prince George's County, Maryland.

Narrative:
-In mid-February 2023, Investigators continued to observe the ping of number 240-772-8433 in the location of Oxon Hill, Maryland. After further investigation, it was determined the phone may be located at 5135 Indian Head Hwy, Oxon Hill, MD 20745. Investigators were able to make contact with Detective Upshaw #4028 of the Prince George's County Police Department District 4. It was discovered on 2/4/2023 while working at the El Amate Restaurant, 2420 University Blvd Hyattsville MD 20783, he was approached a victim who advised an individual pointed a firearm at him. Detective Upshaw was able to identify the suspect as Javier Reyes H/M 2/5/2003 of 3510 Rivera Street Temple Hills, Maryland 20745. This address is the same for Juan Alberto Reyes Caseres; however, their relationship is unknown at this time. Detective Upshaw observed Reyes standing near a blue Ford Fusion bearing Maryland registration 2A34112 where Detective Upshaw was able to observe a black handgun in plain view. The vehicle was seized and transported to PGPD District 4. On 2/9/2023, Detective Upshaw was able to obtain a search warrant for the vehicle and located a black Glock 36 with six (6) .45 caliber ammunition in the magazine and one (1) .45 caliber ammunition in the chamber. In addition, 27 blue pills were located and a blue cellphone. It was discovered the cellphone was in fact using the number 240-772-8433. The cellphone was seized and placed in storage per PGPD policy.

On 2/21/2023, investigators took possession of the phone and will be authoring a search warrant for its content.
  
Case Open.

All events occurred in Prince George's County, Maryland.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeTitle: Supplement #3: Observations of F-150 February and early March 2023
IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
Date of Supplement: March 15, 2023

Author: Sgt. Patrick Lane #5164

Narrative: 
During the winter of 2023, S/T Maldonado and the investigation team identified a dark blue Ford F-150 extended cab pick-up truck with Maryland registration 8ES9488. The investigation team identified as having silver or similar color rocker panels and white lettering on the passenger side.

This vehicle was used by the suspects to meet with confidential informants in February and March. For further information about these incidents and suspects, refer to S/T Maldonado’s supplements. The focus of supplement is other information, including camera footage and GPS tracking information for this vehicle.

The investigation team caused a pole camera to be deployed in the area of 9601 Cottrell Avenue, Silver Spring MD. This was used several times to attempt to observe the movements of target vehicles, including the target silver Camry, and the residence of interest 9601 Cottrell. On March 14, 2023, the investigation team executed a search warrant for GPS tracking on the Ford pickup.

When the F-150 was used during a second controlled purchase in March 2023, I performed a review of the pole camera to attempt to find other times it was in the area of Cottrell Avenue. Notes also included observations of the silver Camry, Maryland registration 1DW8727. Although the registration cannot be confirmed via the pole camera depending on where it is parked, I based these observations on the overall appearance of the vehicle, my familiarity with it, and my familiarity with where it normally parks in the neighborhood.
I performed spot checks for these two vehicles on February 8, 2023 through February 17, 2023.

On February 17, 2023 at 0800 I noted the presence of the Camry, possible for the first time since it has been absent from the area for several weeks. I believe the vehicle may have been damaged based on images from the camera in early January, and its absence may have been caused by it being repaired. It was parked at its usual spot near the intersection of Cottrell and Avenell.

On February 20, 2023 at 1200 hours, I again noted the presence of the Camry.

On February 20, 2023 at 1557 I noted the presence of the Camry and the F-150. I identified the F-150 due to its distinctive rocker panels and my familiarity with its description and where it normally parks at the intersection of Cottrell and Avenell. The F-150 shows up at 1557 hours, parks at intersection of Cottrell and Avenell. A subject gets out and goes over to the passenger seat. Gets back into driver's seat and moves the truck slightly.  Gets out again, goes over to passenger door again. It appears that he gets into the passenger seat. Seems like he just waits there.

On February 20, 2023 at 1616 hours, a subject wearing all black walks into frame from behind the camera, on Cottrell Ave, gets into the driver's seat, they both sit there for a few minutes, and then drive away at about 1620 hours.
Between February 21 and February 23, I performed additional spot checks for these vehicles. Several times on each day, a vehicle I believe to be the Camry is present, but the F-150 is not present.

On February 23, 2023 at 1557 hours, I made the following observations about the F-150: Camry present, F-150 pulls up and parks at corner. I again recognized it due to its distinct rocker panels, my familiarity with its overall description, and where it parks in the neighborhood. At least two people are in it, and they sit in the truck for several minutes. The passenger appears to be wearing red. Driver gets out wearing a black t shirt, green shorts and what looks like black leggings. Walks down Cottrell off camera. Subject appears similar in appearance to Javier Reyes. Passenger stays in passenger seat.

On February 23, 2023 at 1616 hours, driver walks back up the street, gets into the truck, and it leaves the area.


On February 28, 2023 I made additional observations. At 1600 hours, the Camry is present. The F-150 shows up at 1549 hours and parks at the normal corner spot.  Driver sits in vehicle for several minutes. Driver gets out at 1556 hours and walks down Avenell past 9601 Cottrell. A couple of minutes later same subject walks back to the truck and gets in the driver's seat.  Subject sits in driver's seat for a few minutes and then drives away. Unknown at this time if additional parties were in the vehicle.

F-150 returns at 1617 hours. Appears to have two people in it who sit in car for a couple of minutes. At 1620 hours, a subject wearing all black enters frame from area of Avenell next to 9601 Cottrell house, walks up to passenger side of truck, gets in passenger seat. Seems like possibly someone inside the truck switches seats. Truck leaves at 1623 hours.

2-28-2023 at 1800 hours – Camry present, truck not present.

2-28-2023 at 2156 hours – Truck appears to return again. Camera is too dark to make good observations, but you can see a truck with similar physical characteristics drive by the 9601 house and then park in its usual spot at the intersection of Cottrell and Avenel.

3-2-2023 at 1750 hours – Truck drives up facing away from camera and parks at the corner. D/Sgt Jefferson makes in person observations and tag is confirmed by Sgt. Lane checking the camera and zooming in. D/Sgt. Jefferson also notes it has a partially busted back window and later notices that its tag lights are extremely bright. Headlights are also brighter than standard.

Driver is observed wearing black pants with a green stripe, a black sweatshirt with large white lettering. Seems like he is looking for something in the truck because he is moving around and his phone camera flashlight is on.

At 1758 a subject wearing all black walks up Cottrell from off-screen and gets into the passenger side of the truck. Truck drives away shortly after that.

This subject is also later observed after the controlled purchase a nearby WaWa while getting gas and other items.

On March 14, 2023 at approximately 0300 hours, a search warrant for GPS tracking was executed on this vehicle. It was located in the area of 4401 52nd Place, Bladensburg MD. It was observed there several times between March 8, 2023 and March 14, 2023. The below image was captured by myself on March 8, 2023 at approximately 1039 hours. For further details about this search warrant, refer to S/T Maldonado’s supplement. The GPS tracker was attached, and I reviewed the information on March 15, 2023 via a location history report.

On March 14, 2023 at approximately 0905 hours, it appears that the F-150 leaves the neighborhood of 52nd Place, although it does appear to come back shortly thereafter, before it appears to leave the area again at 1030 hours. At 1053 hours, it is in Washington DC. At approximately 1120 hours it is in Virginia in the area of Alban Rd.

It appears to spend the day traveling in Virginia and Washington DC. It returns to Maryland at approximately 1811 hours and is in the area of the Varnum St/52nd Place neighborhood at 1821 hours. At 858 hours it appears to have traveled to a residence near Wooded Way and Wooded Court in the Hillendale area.

By 1938 hours it has traveled to the Rockville area near Parklawn Drive. It appears to travel to several residential areas in Montgomery County.

By 2025 it has traveled to the Cottrell Neighborhood where it can be seen on the Pole Camera. For unknown reasons it remains in the area traveling to the intersection of Avenel Rd and Paula Drive. At 2153 hours it s at the intersection of Avenell Rd and Dilston Rd.
At 2203 hours it has left the neighborhood, and by 2213 it has returned and is again located in the area of Avenel Rd and Paula Dr. At 2219 it is still in the area, although it appears to be leaving. At 2229 hours it appears to be traveling on Randolph Road in the area of Hawkesbury Lane.

At 2249 hours it has returned to the White Oak / Hillendale area.

At 2317, it is back in the area of the 52nd Place residence in Bladensburg. I believe it remains there until March 15, 2023 at approximately 0109 hours when it appears to leave. Between 0109 hours and throughout the early morning, it travels to Montgomery County, making its way to the area of Watkins Mill Road and Paramount Park Drive at approximately 0200 hours. It appears to travel to several residential areas, before finally returning to the 52nd Place residence by 0445 hours.

On March 15, 2023 at approximately 0823 hours it is still in this area, however it appears to leave shortly thereafter as it is out of the neighborhood at 0830 hours.

-Controlled purchase
Narrative:
-Investigators continued attempting to positively identify “Carlos”. Investigators were able identify social media accounts for Javier Reyes, “javii reyes”. In addition, investigators reviewed footage from the covert audio and visual recording devices placed within the confidential informant’s vehicle. After comparing Wawa video footage, Social Media photographs, covert surveillance video, and confidential informant testimony, investigators were able positively identify the dealer from at least the previous two controlled purchases as Javier Reyes. In addition, the 2/4/2023 incident involving PGPD where Javier Reyes was taken into custody and photographed for possession of a firearm and 27 blue pills similar to those seized during the controlled purchases, investigators further identified Javier Reyes.
On 3/8/2023, investigators were contacted by the Montgomery County Police Department Homicide Unit requesting information regarding phone number 301-860-2028. According the detectives, on or about 3/7/2023 in the area of New Hampshire Ave and Oakview Dr in Silver Spring, Maryland, there was a reported fatal shooting. According to a witness, they observed a Hispanic male running towards a blue pickup truck and entering the passenger seat before it drove off. The witness described the pickup truck as a dark colored, older model pick up. They were unable to provide a make, model, or registration. Further investigation revealed the victim made several contacts to number 301-860-2028 prior to the shooting. 
Investigators will be authoring a GPS warrant for the Ford pickup involved in the last few controlled purchases and will be assisting MCPD with additional information regarding the Ford pickup. Investigators believe the suspects were operating this vehicle.  MCPD will be authoring a PEN order for 301-860-2028.
On 3/8/2023 investigators were contacted by the confidential informant who advised “Carlos” is looking to sale 1,000 pills for $10,000, however, “Carlos” advised he may drop the price to $8,000. “Carlos” also communicated to the confidential informant he has an MP5 .22 caliber firearm for sale if they are interested. Later in the day, “Carlos” reached out to the confidential informant who provided a new phone number of 240-615-0276.
Case Open.
All events occurred in Prince George’s County, Maryland.

Scene Processing:  
-Controlled purchase
Narrative:
-On 3/8/2023, “Carlos” contacted the confidential informant via text message with a new number 240-615-0276. “Carlos” confirms he is willing to sell 100 pills for $800. “Carlos” also confirms he has a 380 handgun for $650, MP5 .22 caliber and M&P 15-22 for $1,150 each.
On 3/9/2023, “Carlos” contacts the confidential informant via text message and asks if they are interested in purchasing 1,000 pills and he has Glock 19, 20, 23, 26, 27, and 35 for sell.
On 3/10/2023, “Carlos” contacts the confidential informant via text message using a new number, 240-529-9030.
On 3/10/2023, investigators installed a GPS tracking device on the Ford F-150, which was located at 4401 52nd Bladensburg. Investigators monitor the location of the device, which showed the Ford parked at the Bladensburg location each night and morning.  In addition, “Carlos”, who advised he has changed numbers to 240-529-9030, contacted the confidential informant. On 3/11/2023, “Carlos” asks when the confidential informant will be in the area and he still has firearms to sell.
On 3/14/23, a search warrant obtained by Montgomery County Police Department Homicide Investigator for historical call details and cell site (location information) for the newest number associated with “Carlos”, 240-529-9030. A PEN Register with location information was also obtained for this phone number to have active pings (current location information for the cellular phone) sent to MCP Investigators.

On 3/15/2023, MCPD officers in a plain-clothes capacity were conducting surveillance in reference to this case. Brian Gaitan-Sanchez was observed leaving 4401 52nd Place, Bladensburg, Maryland and entering the driver’s seat of the Ford F-150. Gaitan-Sanchez drives to the Hyattsville District Courthouse. At approximately 1330 hours, MCPD officers observed Javier Reyes inside the courthouse. The plainclothes officer called phone number 240-529-9030 and observed Reyes answer the phone and say “hello”. The MCPD plainclothes officer heard Javier Reyes’ voice over the phone as well as in the hallway as he was only approximately 5 feet away. Subsequently both Reyes and Gaitan-Sanchez were seen in the blue, Ford pickup truck leaving the courthouse.

Investigators shared photos and video footage of Reyes from previous CDS controlled purchases. In addition, PGPD Det. Upshaw provided photos taken during the firearm seizure. MCPD investigators were able to positively identify Reyes.

MCPD Investigators have compared images from the video footage of the pickup truck seen at the homicide to the pickup truck driven to the courthouse and used in the CDS transactions. MCPD investigators were able to positively identify the Ford F-150, which was used during the CDS transactions, and to pick up Reyes from the courthouse.

Investigators also provided photos of Gaitan-Sanchez to MCPD investigators. MCPD investigators confirmed Gaitan-Sanchez has a history of selling scrap metal and pawning. On 2/16/2023, Brian Gaitan-Sanchez drove the Ford F150 to a local scrap yard to sell scrap metal. The transaction weas recorded by the scrapyard with Gaitan-Sanchez’s driver’s license and the F-150’s vehicle information (including the same vehicle registration). Gaitan-Sanchez has also pawned items at pawnshops. According to databases used by police, Gaitan-Sanchez provided the cellphone number 240-821-0365 during his pawn transactions.

On 3/15/2023, the confidential informant was advised to let “Carlos” know they are busy and not in the area. In addition, the confidential informant was advised to ask “Carlos” what type of firearms he has, which he states, a MP5 .22 caliber for sale. After speaking with MCPD, investigators discovered the firearm used was possibly a 380. The confidential informant was instructed to ask if the 380 was still available, “Carlos” advised it was already sold. In addition, “Carlos” advised he is willing to sell 1,000 pills for $8,000.

On 3/16/2023, a search warrant for call detail records/historical location information was obtained by MCPD Investigators for Gaitan-Sanchez’ cellular phone number 240-821-0365. The records received from T-Mobile revealed the following:

-On 3/8/2023, just minutes before the homicide, this cellular phone is on scene of Hampshire Green Lane. This information is consistent with the approximate time the call came into 911 and the video of the truck on scene. It should be noted this cellular phone account is registered to Jose Gaitan (the
father of Brian Gaitan-Sanchez).

On 3/20/2023, “Carlos” contacts the confidential informant via text message using a new number, 202-455-3725.

Investigators continued assisting MCPD with identifying and locating suspects in a homicide investigation. This has included daily consultations with MCPD regarding identification of suspects, suspect vehicles, their vehicles, and their drug activities. Investigators have continually updated MCPD on target telephone numbers as the suspects have changed numbers several times since the murder.

MCPD was also provided access to a pole camera on a target neighborhood which was placed by MSP Technical Assistance Unit and TAU is working to download and save footage from this device to provide MCPD for their potential use in the future, as suspects and the suspect vehicle are seen on camera a few hours before the homicide. MCPD was also provided access to a GPS tracker. MCPD was able to use the pole camera, GPS, and phone information to develop further information regarding their homicide investigation and confirm houses of interest identified by investigators. MCPD investigators drafted arrest warrants for Javier Reyes and Brian Gaitan-Sanchez, search warrants for two residences, and the target vehicle.

On 3/21/2023, investigators met with MCPD investigators to brief for the execution of the warrants. Parties were detained by MCPD without incident and Reyes and Gaitan-Sanchez were taken into custody. Interviews by MCPD are ongoing. During the execution of the warrant, several devices of interest were located and seized. Search of vehicles of interest is pending.

Due to the arrest of the primary suspects in this investigation, this case is closed. If further information regarding this drug trafficking organization is developed, further updates will follow.

Case closed.
All events occurred in Prince George’s County and Montgomery County, Maryland.
